      "lineNbr": 318,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-27T12:16:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No, the contract between the kernel driver is that once PIPE_ERROR_AGAIN is returned, the driver will:\n\n1) not try to send data anymore\n\n2) call onGuestWantWakeOn(PIPE_WAKE_WRITE) to indicate it wants to be woken up when it can send more data. This is where mHostSocket-\u003ewantWrite() is called.\n\n3) the pipe should call signalWake(PIPE_WAKE_WRITE) when the socket allows writing again.\n\nThe dontWantWrite() here is to avoid sending signalWake(PIPE_WAKE_WRITE) events when the driver doesn\u0027t expect them.",
      "parentUuid": "ea03478f_c64bc22d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 318,
        "startChar": 33,
        "endLine": 318,
        "endChar": 46
      },
      "revId": "a4855aacd0c4da8ae5e6bf056564075fde35c8f1",
